Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.76,0:10:00.80,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Welcome to Project Sekai Aftertalk "Find the dream view" Edition!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:05.20,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Good evening everyone, this is Yuki Nakashima, voice of Shiho Hinomori.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.20,0:10:12.58,Shiho,,0,0,0,,In this Aftertalk, we'll recap the event while reading letters that you, the fans, have sent in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.58,0:10:20.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So, how did you like the "Find the dream view" event story, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.02,0:10:22.98,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Good 'need'-vening!*" Good 'need'-vening hahaha.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.98,0:10:27.28,Shiho,,0,0,0,,You know, I think you guys are the only ones who say that back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.28,0:10:29.14,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Thank you for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.14,0:10:35.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Good 'need'-vening" hasn't really caught on among us yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.02,0:10:39.04,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Do you think it'd be alright if we turned this into our official greeting? Hahaha
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.04,0:10:44.66,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Leoni doesn't have a greeting yet like "wonderhoi",
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.66,0:10:51.34,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I just said it on a radio episode once and it seems to have stuck with you guys, so thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.76,0:10:55.18,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Is it okay to make it official? Not sure haha
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.18,0:10:58.07,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Guess I just have to keep pushing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.07,0:11:02.75,Shiho,,0,0,0,,We've actually been using 'Kon-niido' for a pretty long time now, haven't we? www
Comment: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:04.68,Shiho,,0,0,0,,~~~ End Opening Greeting ~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.21,0:12:53.81,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Alright, with that— is it okay to start?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.81,0:12:59.19,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Let's talk about the "Find the dream view" event story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.19,0:13:04.78,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I see in the chat you've all already been saying "the story was awesome", but what did you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.78,0:13:09.11,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Let's look back through the story while reading some of your letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.11,0:13:13.38,Shiho,,0,0,0,,First up, a letter from "Mist-san", thank you for the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.40,0:13:19.30,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"That live performance at the end of the story was peak excitement."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.30,0:13:24.96,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"I was blown away by the new special features added thanks to the 4th Anniversary update."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.96,0:13:31.05,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Even through the screen, I was just as moved as the live audience."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.05,0:13:33.42,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"I thought, 'Leo/need is so awesome!'"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.42,0:13:37.33,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yay~! Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.33,0:13:39.51,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I mean, that performance...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.51,0:13:43.15,Shiho,,0,0,0,,That performance really hit me as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.15,0:13:44.23,Shiho,,0,0,0,,It was way too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.23,0:13:50.96,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Later, I have some stuff I want to talk about for that part of the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.96,0:13:52.68,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but let's save that for later.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.68,0:13:55.26,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Moving onto the next letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.26,0:13:57.95,Shiho,,0,0,0,,From Pusesuki(?)-san, thanks for the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.95,0:14:00.37,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"This story was super exciting!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.37,0:14:05.68,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Especially in Chapter 7, seeing Leoni surrounded by an audience that isn't too familiar with them,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.68,0:14:12.96,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"I got so fired up that I wanted to reach through the screen and shout 'do your best, Leoni!'"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.96,0:14:17.84,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"So when I heard 'star trail' playing, together with the cut-ins, I just ascended."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.84,0:14:22.82,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"I'm interested if you have any stories to share about recording for the event story or song."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.82,0:14:25.46,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.46,0:14:32.14,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad to hear so many of your thoughts about Chapter 7 and questions about recording for the event story and song.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:38.10,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So let's start by watching the much-discussed Chapter 7.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.14,0:14:39.47,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(968,170)}I'm gonna cut out the chapter viewing because tbh Yuki doesn't say too much.\NAlso I don't wanna figure out how to add in the story subs lmao
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.10,0:14:39.47,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Here we go!
Comment: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:44.90,PiP,,0,0,0,,~~~ BEGIN TALKING OVER EPISODE ~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.80,0:14:44.90,PiP,,0,0,0,,Chapter 7 is soooo gooooood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.90,0:14:47.77,PiP,,0,0,0,,The story before it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.11,0:15:10.67,PiP,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's a 15,000-person venue, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.67,0:15:14.97,PiP,,0,0,0,,Maybe Tokyo? Wonder where exactly it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.97,0:15:17.71,PiP,,0,0,0,,Where would there be space for a 15,000-person venue?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.08,0:15:23.71,PiP,,0,0,0,,I think Ariake Arena is around that size.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:26.42,PiP,,0,0,0,,K-Arena is a little bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.42,0:15:29.84,PiP,,0,0,0,,But they're at a venue that big already...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.84,0:15:33.96,PiP,,0,0,0,,But this venue...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.96,0:15:37.88,PiP,,0,0,0,,It's Ariake Arena? Ehhhhh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.88,0:15:40.65,PiP,,0,0,0,,I'm kind of glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.14,0:15:46.01,PiP,,0,0,0,,Isn't that crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.01,0:15:49.01,PiP,,0,0,0,,
Comment: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:48.70,PiP,,0,0,0,,~~~ BEGIN POST EPISODE DISCUSSION ~~~
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.70,0:23:52.71,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Ahhhhhh.... Chapter 7... so peak...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.34,0:23:58.46,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I didn't really talk much, did I. Was too busy just watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.02,0:24:02.09,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Chapter 7 was seriously way too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.09,0:24:11.05,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So with that, we have a comment about this scene from the story production director.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.05,0:24:15.84,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Wait, that's awesome. We're gonna start having these staff commentaries with this mini-renewal.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.84,0:24:16.53,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Let's read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.53,0:24:25.27,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"In this event, we wanted to create a special animation showing that fleeting moment where the Leo/need members all meet eyes."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.27,0:24:32.48,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Chapter 7 continues with depictions of each member's emotional state, so we wanted to not only capture the excitement of the performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.48,0:24:35.77,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"but also focus on the shift in those emotions."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.77,0:24:39.59,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Through this animation, we wanted to convey the four’s shared desire,"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.59,0:24:44.85,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"to reach others with Leo/need’s music;\Nnot just to their audience, but to our players as well."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.85,0:24:51.17,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Also, as a slight change from previous events, we used BGM with vocals this time."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.17,0:24:56.86,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"We wanted to show the girls' music in the most impactful way possible through our visuals,"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.86,0:25:04.22,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"so we created this sequence where the four all meet eyes, the BGM chorus kicks in, the card stills appear, and each character speaks."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.22,0:25:06.59,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"It all comes together for a top notch scene."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.59,0:25:14.45,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"We went through a lot of trial and error on the technical side to deliver the best version of this scene possible, so we hope you enjoy it."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.15,0:25:23.53,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Incredible. Wasn’t that such a great scene, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.07,0:25:34.53,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So for the first BGM with vocals for Leoni, we recorded "star trail".
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.53,0:25:39.69,Shiho,,0,0,0,,This time, we recorded with— we usually record with the same team,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.69,0:25:43.22,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but this time, we recorded with a different team than usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.22,0:25:46.58,Shiho,,0,0,0,,It felt— how should I put this,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.58,0:25:51.33,Shiho,,0,0,0,,recording for this song was more focused on calls from the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.33,0:25:57.09,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I think if you listen closely, Shiho is cheering everyone on in her own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.09,0:25:59.01,Shiho,,0,0,0,,She's going like "hai hai".
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.01,0:26:02.01,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Lots of parts worth taking an extra listen for.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.01,0:26:08.39,Shiho,,0,0,0,,This is, how to say, through and through, a Leo/need song.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.39,0:26:15.38,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Maaaaan, I'm so glad at how well that scene turned out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.38,0:26:22.31,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I mean, using that BGM there though is a bit unfair, isn't it? www
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.31,0:26:25.20,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Like, you can't really help but cry there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.20,0:26:30.37,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I was really just moved by the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.57,0:26:35.89,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah— "Full version when???" Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.89,0:26:39.93,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Not sure if we'll get the chance to do a full version...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.93,0:26:42.87,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Maybe if enough people ask for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.87,0:26:46.53,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Please ask for it. Please and thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.53,0:26:47.49,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Ah—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.49,0:26:48.99,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Ehhhh!!??
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.99,0:26:50.16,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Of course I get nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.16,0:26:53.51,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"I know you have experience, but do you still get nervous on big stages?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.51,0:26:54.42,Shiho,,0,0,0,, "How is it?*"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.51,0:26:58.11,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1109.333,31.333)}*The commenter used "donai" which is a\Nvery Kansai dialect way of asking "how is it (for you)"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.42,0:26:58.11,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Hahahaha thank you for the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.11,0:27:02.21,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I get super nervous. Generally I'm the type to get really nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.21,0:27:06.58,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But actually, for the first time performing on a stage this big,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.58,0:27:12.96,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I definitely think Shiho was a bit nervous, going up on a stage like that not knowing what it would feel like.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.96,0:27:16.47,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But for my first time, instead of feeling nerves, I was like:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.47,0:27:19.84,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"I have no idea what's gonna happen, so I'm not nervous!"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.84,0:27:22.84,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Haha something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.84,0:27:27.54,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Then I actually stepped on stage and was like,\N"oh crap we're actually gonna perform {\i1}here{\i0}?"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.54,0:27:29.91,Shiho,,0,0,0,, {\i1}Then {\i0}I started feeling nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.91,0:27:32.74,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.74,0:27:40.65,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, I don't think I've ever gone out on stage {\i1}not{\i0} feeling a bit nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.65,0:27:44.36,Shiho,,0,0,0,,For one reason or another, I always end up nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.36,0:27:46.84,Shiho,,0,0,0,,And in this story,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.84,0:27:53.22,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Leo/need was the opening act for an audience\Nthat wasn't really familiar with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.22,0:28:02.92,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I've also had that experience before where you can kind of feel that lots of the audience isn't really as familiar with your music.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.92,0:28:10.24,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Somehow you can tell they're going like\N"hmm, I'm not really sure how to vibe to this."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.24,0:28:15.39,Shiho,,0,0,0,,When that happens, sometimes you kind of just want to say "just follow along with us". Myself included.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.39,0:28:20.80,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But, I know exactly what it feels like to have that disconnect with the audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.80,0:28:27.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,which is why the emotions in Chapter 7 were just so incredibly real.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.02,0:28:35.65,Shiho,,0,0,0,,When I first read the script for this story, seeing the slightly critical comments after the band was announced,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.65,0:28:41.74,Shiho,,0,0,0,,or the characters feeling like "maybe we should have practiced even more",
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.74,0:28:43.38,Shiho,,0,0,0,,it felt so relatable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.38,0:28:46.11,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I've felt the same thing so many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.11,0:28:50.70,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I feel the exact same way so often, that I actually started crying just reading the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.70,0:28:52.73,Shiho,,0,0,0,,It really moved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.73,0:28:55.50,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So when it came to recording this chapter—
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.50,0:29:02.52,Shiho,,0,0,0,,for the event stories, we usually individually record one chapter at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.52,0:29:05.65,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Usually we kind of just breeze through each one.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.65,0:29:12.41,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But for Chapter 7, there was so much coming from the heart, so many emotions coming out.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.41,0:29:16.54,Shiho,,0,0,0,,There were so many monologues.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.54,0:29:20.62,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I was directed to "just lay everything out bare."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.46,0:29:26.67,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I said "I got this. Let's do it!" Then recorded Chapter 7 all in one take.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.67,0:29:32.47,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Then they were just like "Ah, okay we got it," and we were done in one go.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.47,0:29:40.97,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I think that just shows how naturally I was able to empathize with the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.97,0:29:47.19,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I think the story did an amazing job capturing this reality of performing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.19,0:29:51.82,Shiho,,0,0,0,,And I really hope that really came through.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.82,0:29:58.49,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I was really surprised we did Chapter 7 all in one take like that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.49,0:30:12.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So, I’d love for you to go back and watch not just that scene, but the whole story from Chapter 1 to 8.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.02,0:30:18.97,Shiho,,0,0,0,,And please check out the side stories for each card, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.40,0:30:23.40,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Such a real story". Definitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.91,0:30:28.53,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Such a good story, and such a good production too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.53,0:30:31.64,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Actually, did you see the card art move a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.64,0:30:34.09,Shiho,,0,0,0,,That really made that scene hit harder, didn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.09,0:30:41.56,Shiho,,0,0,0,,This is just a bit of wishful thinking, but wouldn't it be great if all cards could have something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.56,0:30:46.51,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Like maybe just a cool little animation when\N you pull them, even if it's just for 4 stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.51,0:30:49.21,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I’m putting that out into the universe right now www
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.21,0:30:52.89,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Alright then, that's all we have for our story discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.89,0:31:00.50,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So in a previous letter, we had a question about any stories from recording the event song.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.50,0:31:16.45,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1117.334,20.667)}Also gonna cut this, don't wanna deal with copyright.\NJust go watch it on official YouTube haha
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.50,0:31:08.56,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So first we’ll watch the 2DMV for the event song "Sympathy" together, written for us by Eve-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.56,0:31:12.16,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Then we’ll talk about some of the stories from the recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.16,0:31:16.45,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So let’s start by watching the MV. Enjoy!
Comment: 0,0:34:15.52,0:34:18.52,Shiho,,0,0,0,,~~~ START SYMPATHY TALK ~~~rr
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.52,0:34:25.76,Shiho,,0,0,0,,You just listened to "Sympathy" by Eve-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.76,0:34:30.98,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Ahh, such a good song, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.98,0:34:37.36,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So actually, this was the first song I ever had to do a "key check" for.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.36,0:34:43.06,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So I think you can tell if you've heard some of Eve-san's other songs,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.06,0:34:48.12,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but their songs have both super low- and high-pitched parts.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.12,0:34:52.94,Shiho,,0,0,0,,They're able to create songs that bring together so many different registers.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.84,0:34:58.26,Shiho,,0,0,0,,They told me "this song will be just like that,"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.26,0:35:00.20,Shiho,,0,0,0,,so they asked me to do a key check.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.20,0:35:04.60,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So I said "oh, okay, got it."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.60,0:35:07.88,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But when I asked why we're going to do one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.88,0:35:15.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Shiho usually sings with a pretty low voice in a lot of the songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.02,0:35:17.34,Shiho,,0,0,0,,It does also fit her image well.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.34,0:35:23.52,Shiho,,0,0,0,,We were worried that if I were to sing too high, it might drift away from that image somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.52,0:35:26.40,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So in the chorus,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.40,0:35:29.18,Shiho,,0,0,0,,the part that goes "kodamashite~",
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.40,0:35:29.18,Ruby Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1152,974)}"let it ring out"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.18,0:35:33.28,Shiho,,0,0,0,,they wanted me to really belt it out in my chest voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.28,0:35:39.98,Shiho,,0,0,0,,We were like, "Is there a key that would let you hit those belt notes while also bringing out those low-pitched sounds?"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.98,0:35:41.42,Shiho,,0,0,0,,In the end, they let me decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.42,0:35:47.84,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I told them the original key seemed fine, so we stuck with the original key.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.84,0:35:51.58,Shiho,,0,0,0,,If we lowered it, the pre-chorus would’ve been too low.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.58,0:35:56.06,Shiho,,0,0,0,,If it was just me, I might have been able to hit it, but the other members might have struggled.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.06,0:36:00.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But I figured with the original key, I could really belt out the chorus,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.02,0:36:03.78,Shiho,,0,0,0,,and even though the high notes in the second half are pretty up there,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.78,0:36:10.06,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I told them "I can make it work," and we went with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.06,0:36:16.96,Shiho,,0,0,0,,You can hear this in other songs too, like "Peaky Peaky",
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.96,0:36:18.96,Shiho,,0,0,0,,if you listen again, you'll see what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.96,0:36:24.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,In the Another Vocal version, I think, for KAITO's parts,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.96,0:36:33.68,Shiho,,0,0,0,,we ended up using just the original range, without going an octave down.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.68,0:36:38.44,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But for this session, we actually recorded versions both an octave down and in the same key as KAITO.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.44,0:36:44.36,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Then usually, the staff decides which version to use in the final mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.36,0:36:47.54,Shiho,,0,0,0,,We always record extra takes like that just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.54,0:36:54.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But then in that April Fools' cover we did for "Envy Baby,"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.02,0:36:58.22,Shiho,,0,0,0,,they actually ended up using {\b1}both{\b0} versions.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.22,0:37:01.22,Shiho,,0,0,0,,In the "haifai koiseyo raiaia" part,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.22,0:37:01.22,Ruby Text,,0,0,0,,{\fscx80\pos(970.667,971.333)}{\fscy80}{\pos(965.333,1006)}"fall in a high-fi love lie-ai-a"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.22,0:37:06.88,Shiho,,0,0,0,,at first, they wanted me to record that in the original key,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.88,0:37:09.70,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but I was like "can I really sing this as Shiho?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.70,0:37:13.82,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I was like "could we record an octave down {\i1}just in case{\i0}?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.82,0:37:16.16,Shiho,,0,0,0,,And it turns out they used both!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.16,0:37:17.56,Shiho,,0,0,0,,That can happen sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.56,0:37:19.62,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Shiho, sometimes- yeah yeah yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.62,0:37:23.18,Shiho,,0,0,0,,There are cases where both can be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.18,0:37:25.20,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.20,0:37:26.82,Shiho,,0,0,0,,how to put it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.82,0:37:29.60,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I'm always really excited to see how the final mix turns out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.60,0:37:36.12,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Now, Eve-san wasn't actually present during the recording session this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.12,0:37:39.00,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but after I’d finished recording all the parts for "Sympathy,"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.00,0:37:41.52,Shiho,,0,0,0,,there was this one part....
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.52,0:37:45.72,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I think it was a part where I’d recorded an octave-down track...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.72,0:37:47.80,Shiho,,0,0,0,,a harmony, if I remember correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.80,0:37:55.94,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Well, Eve-san requested that I also record a high-octave harmony for that same section.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.94,0:37:59.30,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So I went back in for some extra takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.30,0:38:04.36,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we recorded a lot of extra takes for this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.36,0:38:09.60,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So try listening to it really closely next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.00,0:38:17.06,Shiho,,0,0,0,,"Yeah, the harmonies are so good". Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.06,0:38:21.56,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we did a lot of extra takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.56,0:38:24.86,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Right? I'm really glad we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.86,0:38:30.48,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Man, talking about it like this really makes it sink in for me how well "Sympathy" actually came together.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.48,0:38:37.48,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I'm really glad for the chance to share all these behind-the-scenes stories with you guys too. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.48,0:38:43.86,Shiho,,0,0,0,,The MV is on the official YouTube channel, so please listen to it again if you have the chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.86,0:38:47.46,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Please also try out the song in game as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.46,0:38:50.26,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yep. Please listen to it a lot~
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.70,0:38:56.58,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the other VAs have had similar experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.58,0:39:06.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but having to do a key check for the first time for Shiho's event song was a real surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.90,0:39:13.32,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, "Aoiro Enogu" is super high-pitched!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.70,0:39:17.82,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I just saw a comment about that and had to mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.82,0:39:20.82,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that song is super high.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.92,0:39:28.54,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I'll keep working to show many different sides of Shiho-chan, so please look forward to what's coming up!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.54,0:39:31.80,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So with that, I felt like this really flew by www
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.80,0:39:36.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,but that's all for this Aftertalk "Find the dream view" Edition!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.32,0:39:40.48,Shiho,,0,0,0,,How was it, everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.48,0:39:41.74,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Time really flew by!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.74,0:39:45.46,Shiho,,0,0,0,,We did a bit of a mini-renewal today. From reading some of your fan letters,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.46,0:39:48.80,Shiho,,0,0,0,,hearing some commentary from the staff,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.80,0:39:52.28,Shiho,,0,0,0,,and talking about some behind-the-scenes, we covered a lot of ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.28,0:39:54.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,It went by so quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.46,0:39:59.36,Shiho,,0,0,0,,We'll be sticking with the format from here on,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.36,0:40:04.54,Shiho,,0,0,0,,so please check out the submissions channel Discord,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.54,0:40:09.92,Shiho,,0,0,0,,and feel free to send your questions— not questions, your suggestions and such.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.36,0:40:15.66,Shiho,,0,0,0,,That really did go by so quick, didn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.66,0:40:20.14,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Man, I'm so curious about how Leo/need is going to move forward from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.14,0:40:27.92,Shiho,,0,0,0,,This event really reaffirmed, or actually, helped me rediscover, exactly what Shiho wants to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.92,0:40:35.14,Shiho,,0,0,0,,But somehow, Saki-chan looked just a little "unsettled" at the end of the story, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.14,0:40:40.90,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Well, "unsettled" is a bit of a strong word, more like she looked like something was still on her mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.90,0:40:49.24,Shiho,,0,0,0,,I'm very curious as to what's in store next, so please keep watching over them, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.24,0:40:55.18,Shiho,,0,0,0,,So with that, for everyone not finished with this event's story,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.18,0:41:04.00,Shiho,,0,0,0,,you'll be able to watch all chapters in the archive once the next event starts, so please do read it!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.00,0:41:08.94,Shiho,,0,0,0,,As we mentioned earlier, we're always looking for letters for the Aftertalks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.94,0:41:16.46,Shiho,,0,0,0,,You can submit them in the submissions channel on the official Project Sekai Discord.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.46,0:41:20.76,Shiho,,0,0,0,,If you have any thoughts for the next Aftertalk, we'd love to hear them!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.76,0:41:24.35,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Please keep your messages related to the events.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.35,0:41:28.39,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Well, that's all for today! See you again next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.39,0:41:30.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,Bye bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.02,0:41:33.02,Shiho,,0,0,0,,
